<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>{{ meta.title }}</title>
<style>
  /* Large digital canvas — the overview table is wide (12 columns) and the fonts
     are large (3x the original sizes); A4 cannot hold it without wrapping, so we
     use one generous landscape sheet with comfortable left/right margins. */
  @page { size: 720mm 450mm; margin: 22mm 30mm 24mm 30mm; }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body {
    font-family: "Segoe UI", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #1f2a37; font-size: 31px; line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ---- header (centred) ---- */
  .header { text-align: center; border-bottom: 7px solid #0b3d61; padding-bottom: 18px; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  h1 { font-size: 62px; margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #0b3d61; letter-spacing: .5px; }
  .sub { color: #5b6b7b; font-size: 31px; }
  .win { color: #c0392b; font-weight: 700; }            /* reporting-window dates in red */
  .meta-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; gap: 8px 46px;
               margin-top: 16px; font-size: 28px; color: #34465a; }
  .meta-grid b { color: #0b3d61; }

  h2 { font-size: 41px; margin: 8px 0 14px 0; color: #0b3d61; text-align: center; }

  /* ---- table ---- */
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 8px 0; page-break-inside: auto;
          table-layout: fixed; }
  thead { display: table-header-group; }
  tr { page-break-inside: avoid; }
  th { background: linear-gradient(180deg, #134e7a 0%, #0b3d61 100%); color: #fff;
       text-align: center; padding: 12px 10px; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 600;
       overflow-wrap: break-word; border-right: 1px solid #24608a; }
  th.l { text-align: left; }
  td { padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 2px solid #e4e9ef; font-size: 27px;
       vertical-align: middle; overflow-wrap: break-word; }
  td.c { text-align: center; }
  td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  tbody tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #f1f7fc; }
  tbody tr:hover td { background: #e7f1fa; }
  td.reg { font-weight: 700; color: #0b3d61; text-align: center; }
  td.op { color: #2b3a4a; }
  .muted { color: #9aa6b2; }

  /* energy-type pill */
  .etype { display: inline-block; padding: 3px 16px; border-radius: 16px;
           font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px; }
  .etype.ev { background: #e3f6ea; color: #0a7d3d; }
  .etype.diesel { background: #fdecd2; color: #b3600a; }

  /* latest-data recency colouring */
  .lt-fresh { color: #0a7d3d; font-weight: 600; }       /* data seen inside the window */
  .lt-stale { color: #b3600a; font-weight: 600; }       /* last seen before the window */
  .lt-none  { color: #9aa6b2; }                         /* source never produced data */

  .legend { text-align: center; margin: 14px 0 0 0; font-size: 24px; color: #5b6b7b; }
  .legend span { margin: 0 14px; }
  .dot { display: inline-block; width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 50%;
         vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 6px; }
  .note { margin-top: 22px; padding-top: 14px; border-top: 2px solid #d7e0ea;
          color: #6b7886; font-size: 24px; }
  .footer-src { color: #9aa6b2; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 6px; text-align: center; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="header">
  <h1>{{ meta.title }}</h1>
  <div class="sub">Reporting window <span class="win">{{ meta.window_start }} &rarr; {{ meta.window_end }}</span>
    &middot; cadence: {{ meta.cadence }} ({{ meta.lookback_days }}-day lookback)</div>
  <div class="meta-grid">
    <span><b>Generated (UTC):</b> {{ meta.generated_utc }}</span>
    <span><b>Toolkit version:</b> {{ meta.version }}</span>
    <span><b>Vehicles watched:</b> {{ meta.n_vehicles }}</span>
    <span><b>Next run (UTC):</b> {{ meta.next_due }}</span>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Fleet data-collection overview</h2>
<table>
  <colgroup>
    <col style="width:6%"><col style="width:9%"><col style="width:9.5%"><col style="width:6%">
    <col style="width:7%"><col style="width:6.5%"><col style="width:6%">
    <col style="width:5%"><col style="width:5.5%"><col style="width:6%"><col style="width:6.5%">
    <col style="width:7.5%"><col style="width:7.5%"><col style="width:7.5%">
  </colgroup>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Vehicle</th><th class="l">Operator</th><th class="l">Make / Model</th><th>Energy type</th>
      <th>Telematics data</th><th>SRF logger</th><th>Charger data</th>
      <th>Trips</th><th>Charges</th><th>Active days</th><th>Distance (km)</th>
      <th>Latest telematics</th><th>Latest SRF logger</th><th>Latest charger</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for v in fleet %}
    <tr>
      <td class="reg">{{ v.reg }}</td>
      <td class="op">{{ v.operator }}</td>
      <td>{{ v.model }}</td>
      <td class="c"><span class="etype {{ 'ev' if v.energy_type == 'EV' else 'diesel' }}">{{ v.energy_type }}</span></td>
      <td class="c{{ ' muted' if v.telematics == '—' else '' }}">{{ v.telematics }}</td>
      <td class="c{{ ' muted' if v.logger == '—' else '' }}">{{ v.logger }}</td>
      <td class="c{{ ' muted' if v.charger == '—' else '' }}">{{ v.charger }}</td>
      <td class="c">{{ v.n_trips }}</td>
      <td class="c">{{ v.n_charges }}</td>
      <td class="c">{{ v.active_days }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ v.distance }}</td>
      <td class="c lt-{{ v.latest_tel.cls }}">{{ v.latest_tel.text }}</td>
      <td class="c lt-{{ v.latest_log.cls }}">{{ v.latest_log.text }}</td>
      <td class="c lt-{{ v.latest_chg.cls }}">{{ v.latest_chg.text }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<div class="legend">
  <span><span class="dot" style="background:#0a7d3d"></span>data in this window</span>
  <span><span class="dot" style="background:#b3600a"></span>last seen before this window</span>
  <span><span class="dot" style="background:#9aa6b2"></span>— never collected</span>
</div>

<div class="note">
  <b>Method.</b> For each watched vehicle the monitor extends the canonical report database
  ({{ meta.version }}) forward in time using jolt_toolkit — generating reports only for periods
  <i>after</i> the latest existing coverage, never overwriting any existing report or raw-data file
  (append-only). The data-availability dashboard is refreshed from the same database.
  <i>Telematics data</i> / <i>SRF logger</i> = number of legs in the reporting window backed by each
  SRF data source; <i>Charger data</i> = number of charge-point transactions
  (<code>raw_charger/charger_transactions.csv</code>) recorded in the window;
  <i>Latest telematics</i> / <i>Latest SRF logger</i> / <i>Latest charger</i> = the most recent time each
  source produced data (green = inside this window, amber = an earlier date, — = never seen).
  <div class="footer-src">JOLT — Joint Operators Logistics Trial · data-collection-monitor · generated {{ meta.generated_utc }} UTC</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
